  "name": "rotate_xfrm_reference",
  "description": "Cross-engine pin for the unified xfrm.transform rotate apply (applyTRS). Reuses the frozen reference golden from a real rotate-ring handle capture (top face, +Y axis, 60 deg), but applies it through the xfrm.transform Euler path (tool.set rotate / tool.attr rotate RY / tool.doApply) instead of the rotate_about primitive \u2014 so it exercises the REFACTORED geometry path against the reference engine output. Only the Y-axis case is reproducible this way: a Y rotation is invariant to the pivot Y-component, so ACEN.Auto (top-face centroid 0,0.5,0) yields the same result as the captured origin pivot. Combined with test_rotate_drag_parity (drag==numeric==applyTRS) this gives drag==reference transitively.",
